x4freetext: M.Stefanon
F.Corvi
90 MeV pulsed electron linac.
35 nsec burst width, 400 Hz repetition frequency,
average beam power ~3kW .
23 g HfO(2) in 10-cm-diameter
thin-walled Al disk.
50 cm3 volume. Resolution 9.5 keV at 6.2 MeV .
To detect capture gamma-rays in the range
Energy and intensity calibration by thermal neutron
capture in Cl(n,gamma) and Au(n,gamma) at 4.9 eV
resonance.
Additional checking by capture lines from Al,Fe,Pb in
background spectrum .
For neutron energies measurement.
Flight path 13 m .
Relative neutron energy resolution (FWHM) - 0.5% .
Measurement time 220 hr .
Intensities are average for two normalizations:
-  by Cl(n,gamma) at thermal neutrons from G.D.Loper+,
yielded an intensity 1.18 gammas/100captures in Hf-177
for 6110.8 keV transition, compared with 0.82 and 1.14
gammas/100captures from thermal data of Namenson+ and
Rasmunsen+  .
- comparing gamma-rays in 8.88 eV resonance with those
in 4.90 eV Au resonance; 5.26 gammas/100captures for
6252 keV  transition in Au (measured by Kane) was used.
Using differences between the positions of
primary transitions (deduced from data on final state
energies of Fogelberg+ and Coceva+), the least-square
fitting of spectra was done. Intensities Iij were
determined from resonance areas Aij of gamma
transition of resonance Ei to the low-lying ste Ej,
detection efficiency EPS , relative capture yield Ci :
Iij=K*Aij/(Ci*EPSi*EPSj), where
K - derived from calibration procedure.
Calibration uncertainty
M.M.
Of authors. Spin J = 3, 4 for 66.8 eV resonance.
